are_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — the algebraic counterpart of iter-036, transporting finiteness rather than finrank across the corner-bridge, via Mathlib's $\Module.\mathtt{Finite.equiv}$. Iter-038 → iter-046 build the H⁰ Module.Finite ladder (curve specialisations + carrier predicates + Stein input + global-sections evaluation iso + producer chain end-to-end for $\IsHModuleHomFinite\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$); iter-047 lays foundational parameterised Čech infrastructure; iter-048 appends the Čech-side acyclicity carrier predicate and abstract consumer; iter-049 appends the top-supremum HModule transport (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top_curve}) — the universe $u \to u+1$ bridge that lets iter-053+ ultimately consume iter-048's $\Subsingleton$ on $\HModulePrime$ at the lattice supremum to derive the genus carrier $\Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ at universe $u+1$; iter-050 packages the Čech-vs-derived comparison iso as a $\Prop$-valued typeclass $\Scheme.\HasCechToHModuleIso$ with $\Classical.\mathtt{choice}$-based extractor (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_cechToHModuleIso}) and instance-driven \emph{top-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top_curve}); iter-051 appends the symmetric instance-driven \emph{intermediate-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U))$ at universe $u$; iter-052 appends the generalised rewrite-bridge $\bigsqcup\mathcal U = U$ consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,U)$ on an arbitrary open $U$ under the equality hypothesis; iter-053 appends the existence-bundled affine cover carrier $\HasAffineCechAcyclicCover$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HasAffineCechAcyclicCover}) and the producer $\mathtt{instance}\,\mathtt{instIsAffineHModuleVanishing\_of\_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_instIsAffineHModuleVanishing_of_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover}) — converting iter-040's $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing$ from "user-suppliable hypothesis" to "instance-synthesizable from a single carrier hypothesis", so iter-054+ needs to instantiate ONE class (the carrier) rather than three intertwined obligations; iter-054 appends foundational basic-open cover infrastructure $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_basicOpenCover}), $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_supr\_of\_span\_eq\_top}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_supr_of_span_eq_top}), $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_isAffineOpen}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_isAffineOpen}) — wrapping Mathlib's basic-open cover lemmas into project conventions for iter-055+ to call directly; iter-055 appends the existence-form producer $\mathtt{hasAffineCechAcyclicCover\_of\_basicOpen}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen}) and curve specialisation $\mathtt{hasAffineCechAcyclicCover\_of\_basicOpen\_curve}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen_curve}) — converting per-affine basic-open evidence into iter-053's existence-bundled carrier shape; iter-056 appends pairwise basic-open intersection helpers $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_inter\_eq\_basicOpen\_mul}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_inter_eq_basicOpen_mul}) and $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_inter\_isAffineOpen}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_inter_isAffineOpen}) — packaging the binary-intersection identification + affine-membership transport for iter-057+ Čech-evaluation; iter-