\subsection{N-ary basic-open intersection as a localization (iter-059)}

Iter-059 (this iteration) appends a single thin scaffolding step that packages Mathlib's $\mathtt{IsAffineOpen.isLocalization\_of\_eq\_basicOpen}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/AffineScheme.lean} L716) at the $n$-ary basic-open intersection. Mathlib's lemma signature is
\[
  \mathtt{include}\;h_U\,\;\;\IsAffineOpen\,U \;\Longrightarrow\;
  \forall\,f \in \Gamma(X, U),\;
  \forall\,\{V : X.\mathtt{Opens}\},\;
  \forall\,(i : V \to U),\;
  V = X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f \;\Longrightarrow\;
  @\IsLocalization.\mathtt{Away}\;\_\;\_\;f\;\Gamma(X, V)\;\_\;((X.\mathtt{presheaf}.\mathtt{map}\,i^{\op}).\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{toAlgebra}),
\]
with the conclusion type \emph{explicitly} carrying its $\Algebra$ instance as $((X.\mathtt{presheaf}.\mathtt{map}\,i^{\op}).\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{toAlgebra})$. The explicit $@$-binding is essential because Mathlib's default $\algebra\_section\_section\_basicOpen$ instance (\texttt{Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/Scheme.lean} L724) only fires for the syntactic form $\Gamma(X, X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f)$, \emph{not} for an arbitrary $V$ definitionally equal to $X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f$. The plan-agent verified in the iter-058 pass that a project-local theorem stated with \emph{inferred} algebra fails at the type-signature with `failed to synthesize instance of type class Algebra` --- so the localization theorem must thread the explicit algebra structure $((C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{presheaf}.\mathtt{map}\,i^{\op}).\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{toAlgebra})$ in the conclusion type, matching Mathlib's signature.

\textbf{Why now}: iter-058 closed the inclusion $V \le U$ helper; iter-057 closed the equality $V = X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,(\prod_{i \in t} i.1)$ helper; iter-053 closed the carrier predicate that the iter-060+ Koszul argument will instantiate. Iter-059 ties iter-057 + iter-058 together by actually \emph{invoking} Mathlib's $\mathtt{isLocalization\_of\_eq\_basicOpen}$ to land $@\IsLocalization.\mathtt{Away}\,(\prod_{i \in t} i.1)\,\Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, t.\mathtt{inf'}\,h\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s))$ as a single named theorem the iter-060+ Koszul evaluation can refer to without re-deriving the inclusion + equality at each call site.

\textbf{Strategic value}: this is the last thin foundational scaffolding step on the affine basic-open identification side. After iter-059 lands, the iter-060+ substantive Koszul branch has all four pieces of the localization argument packaged as named declarations: (i) the cover constructor $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}$ (iter-054); (ii) the affine-membership $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_isAffineOpen}$ (iter-057); (iii) the inclusion $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_le}$ (iter-058); (iv) the localization $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_isLocalization}$ (iter-059). The iter-060+ obligation is the actually-substantive content: chain these into a complex-level acyclicity proof via the \emph{extra-degeneracy} engine, see the iter-060+ scoping section below.

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[$N$-ary basic-open intersection is a localization, iter-059]
  \label{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_isLocalization}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.basicOpenCover_finset_inf'_isLocalization}
  \uses{def:Scheme_basicOpenCover, thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_eq_basicOpen_prod, thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_le}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathtt{of}\,k))$, $U$ an affine open of $C.\mathtt{left}$ (with witness $h_U : \IsAffineOpen\,U$), $s \subseteq \Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$, $t : \mathtt{Finset}\,s$, and $h : t.\mathtt{Nonempty}$. Then, writing $V := t.\mathtt{inf'}\,h\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s)$ for the $n$-ary intersection of basic-open cover members and $f := \prod_{i \in t} i.1$ for the product of generators,
  \[
    @\IsLocalization.\mathtt{Away}\;\_\;\_\;f\;\Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, V)\;\_\;((C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{presheaf}.\mathtt{map}\,(\mathtt{homOfLE}\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_le}\,s\,t\,h))^{\op}).\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{toAlgebra}).
  \]
  That is, the n-ary basic-open intersection's structure sheaf $\Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, V)$ is the localisation of $\Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$ away from the product $f = \prod_{i \in t} i.1$, with the algebra structure coming from the presheaf restriction map along the inclusion $V \le U$.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}\leanok
  Term-mode invocation of Mathlib's $\IsAffineOpen.\mathtt{isLocalization\_of\_eq\_basicOpen}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/AffineScheme.lean} L716) with $f := \prod_{i \in t} i.1$, $V := t.\mathtt{inf'}\,h\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s)$, $i := \mathtt{homOfLE}\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_le}\,s\,t\,h)$, and equality witness $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_eq\_basicOpen\_prod}\,s\,t\,h : V = C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f$. Body: $h_U.\mathtt{isLocalization\_of\_eq\_basicOpen}\,\_\,(\mathtt{homOfLE}\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_le}\,s\,t\,h))\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_eq\_basicOpen\_prod}\,s\,t\,h)$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-059 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms $[\propext, \Classical.\mathtt{choice}, \Quot.\mathtt{sound}]$.
\end{proof}

